<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HEAT VENTILATION AIR CONDITIONING (HVAC), Orifice Tube System, Pre-March 2007 - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300,
        4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700, 8500, 8600 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - A/C COMPRESSOR/CLUTCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1602553" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>A/C COMPRESSOR/CLUTCH</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Refer to
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1602519">Figure 19</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f16025b3">Figure 20</hotlnk>
                        while performing the following Remove and Install procedures.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discharge the A/C system. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602528.xml" xrefid="hl1602528">DISCHARGING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl1602528"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove or loosen compressor belt.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect compressor clutch wiring connector at compressor (1).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect refrigerant line fittings (2 and 3) at compressor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove compressor mounting bolts, noting the locations of any brackets secured by the
                    mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove compressor/clutch assembly from the engine.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602519" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/g1602519b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. A/C Compressor</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. A/C COMPRESSOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. DISCHARGE PORT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SUCTION PORT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f16025B3" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/g16025B3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Compressor Mounting Locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. A/C COMPRESSOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Verify that the clutch is installed on the compressor before performing the following
                        installation procedure.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the system is to be flushed or purged, perform that operation before reassembling the
                    system. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602525.xml" xrefid="hl1602525">PURGING OR FLUSHING THE AIR CONDITIONING
                        SYSTEM
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl1602525"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Before installing the compressor, refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602526.xml" xrefid="hl1602526">OIL FILL GUIDELINES</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="hl1602526"/>. The oil shipped in new compressors must be drained when determining the
                    correct amount of refrigerant oil to be added to the system.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install compressor assembly (1) including any brackets previously secured by the
                    compressor mounting bolts. Tighten to 23 - 29 N.m (16.9 - 21.4 lbf-ft).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Always lubricate O-rings with mineral-based oil during installation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using new O-rings and C-plates connect refrigerant line fittings (2 and 3) at
                    compressor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect compressor clutch wiring connector to engine harness.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and align compressor belt.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Recharge the system. Refer to:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602529.xml" xrefid="hl1602529">EVACUATING THE SYSTEM</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="hl1602529"/>; and
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">
                        <hotlnk document="s16025_HL1602530.xml" xrefid="hl1602530">CHARGING THE AIR CONDITIONING
                            SYSTEM
                        </hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="hl1602530"/>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
